Maven Java Web Application: CI/CD Pipeline to Tomcat

Overview
Java web application built with Maven. Demonstrates an automated CI/CD pipeline from source control to deployment on Apache Tomcat.

Tech Stack
Language: Java JDK 21 LTS
Build Tool: Apache Maven 3.9.6
CI/CD: Jenkins
Code Quality: SonarQube 2026.1 LTA
Deployment: Apache Tomcat 10.1
Containerization: Docker
Infrastructure: AWS EC2 or Amazon EKS

Pipeline Workflow
1. Commit: Code pushed to GitHub triggers Jenkins via webhook
2. Build: Maven runs unit tests and packages .war artifact with mvn clean package
3. Analysis: SonarQube performs static application security testing and quality gate check
4. Containerization: Docker multi-stage build packages .war with Tomcat 10.1
5. Deployment: Container deployed to Tomcat on AWS

Getting Started

Prerequisites
JDK 21
Maven 3.9.6
Docker Desktop

Build Locally
git clone https://github.com/JimmyT96/java-cicd-jenkins-sonar.git
cd java-cicd-jenkins-sonar
mvn clean package

Artifact is generated in /target directory.

Run with Docker
docker build -t maven-web-app:v2 .
docker run -p 8080:8080 maven-web-app:v2

Application deploys to Tomcat and is accessible at http://localhost:8080

